=== Architect fix-cycle entry (2026-07-05) ===

Trigger: Tester E2E pass surfaced two gaps in internal/llm/openai.go —
(1) parseRetryAfter returns 0 unconditionally (no Retry-After header read),
(2) ErrCategoryOther conflates auth failures (401) with transient network errors.

Fix 1 — Retry-After capture:

Chose Option (a): custom http.RoundTripper wrapping go-openai's HTTP client.
- New types: retryAfterCapture (thread-safe, stores Retry-After duration),
  captureTransport (wraps http.DefaultTransport, reads Retry-After on 429),
  parseHTTPRetryAfter (parses integer-seconds and HTTP-date formats).
- OpenAIClient gains a capture field, initialized in NewOpenAIClient.
- Call() sets config.HTTPClient with the capture transport.
- classifyError becomes a method on *OpenAIClient, reads capture via
  getAndReset() instead of calling the stub parseRetryAfter(apiErr).
- No new LLMError fields needed — existing RetryAfter field carries the value.
- Rejected Option (b) (fork go-openai) and Option (c) (parse from body).

Fix 2 — Error category split:

Replaced ErrCategoryOther with ErrCategoryAuth + ErrCategoryUnknown.
- ErrCategoryAuth: HTTP 401, 402/403 non-quota. Halt immediately —
  retrying an auth failure will never succeed.
- ErrCategoryUnknown: everything else (5xx, network/DNS/TLS, RequestError,
  unexpected status codes). Bounded exponential backoff, same as Timeout.
- Extended spec §8 retry table with two new rows defining behavior for
  both categories.
- No new LLMError fields — StatusCode + Err chain carry enough context.

Files changed: internal/llm/llm.go (enum constants + comments),
internal/llm/openai.go (transport wrapper + capture + method-ified
classifyError + updated switch), internal/llm/llm_test.go (category
test cases), e2e/phase1_test.go (BadAuth test expectation).

=== Builder fix-cycle entry (2026-07-05) ===

Deliverable: code changes implementing architect's Fix Cycle 1 decisions.

What changed:

1. internal/llm/llm.go — Enum constants:
   - Renamed ErrCategoryOther → ErrCategoryUnknown (unclassified/unexpected)
   - Added ErrCategoryAuth (HTTP 401, 402/403 non-quota)
   - ErrCategoryMalformed moved from iota=4 to iota=5
   All existing test references updated to match.

2. internal/llm/openai.go — Retry-After capture:
   - Added retryAfterCapture (thread-safe, stores Retry-After duration, resets on read)
   - Added captureTransport (custom http.RoundTripper wrapping http.DefaultTransport,
     reads Retry-After header from 429 responses, stores in retryAfterCapture)
   - Added parseHTTPRetryAfter (parses integer-seconds and RFC1123 HTTP-date formats)
   - OpenAIClient gains capture *retryAfterCapture field, initialized in NewOpenAIClient
   - Call() sets config.HTTPClient with captureTransport before creating go-openai client
   - classifyError is now a method on *OpenAIClient, reads capture via
     c.capture.getAndReset() on the 429 path
   - Removed the stub parseRetryAfter(*goopenai.APIError) — no longer needed

3. internal/llm/openai.go — Error category switch:
   - Split the grouped case 400/401/402/403 into individual cases per architect's mapping:
     * 401 → ErrCategoryAuth (any body, halt immediately)
     * 402 → quota check → ErrCategoryQuota or ErrCategoryAuth
     * 403 → quota check → ErrCategoryQuota or ErrCategoryAuth
     * 400 → quota check → ErrCategoryQuota or ErrCategoryUnknown
   - default (5xx, other unexpected status codes) → ErrCategoryUnknown
   - RequestError (network/DNS/TLS) → ErrCategoryUnknown
   - Fallback → ErrCategoryUnknown

4. internal/llm/llm_test.go:
   - Updated "other" test case → "unknown" with ErrCategoryUnknown
   - Added new "auth" test case with ErrCategoryAuth

5. e2e/phase1_test.go:
   - TestE2E_OpenAIClient_BadAuth: expected category changed from
     ErrCategoryOther → ErrCategoryAuth

Test results:
